

From: Daniel Barboza <daniel.barboza@oss.qualcomm.com>

Add the LT variant as well:

(bool >= A) < A -> bool < A

Bootstrapped on x86, aarch64 and rv64.
Regression tested in x86 and aarch64.

	PR tree-optimization/119422

gcc/ChangeLog:

	* match.pd(`(bool >= A) >= A -> bool >= A`): New pattern.
	(`(bool >= A) < A -> bool < A`): New pattern.

gcc/testsuite/ChangeLog:

	* gcc.dg/tree-ssa/pr119422-2.c: New test.
	* gcc.dg/tree-ssa/pr119422.c: New test.
---

Changes from v1:
- add LE pattern
- add INTEGRAL_TYPE_P check before TYPE_UNSIGNED
- v1 link: https://gcc.gnu.org/pipermail/gcc-patches/2026-March/709756.html

